&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A team that is aligned and patient-focused creates a great environment for patients, and for you as a member of the team. This is what we strive to be and who we want to join us in providing the best care possible for patients to help our communities be healthier, feel better, and smile with confidence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are seeking an Assisted Dental Hygienist that shares our passion for patient care and education, and who thrives in a fast-paced, team-based care model. This role works in a dual-provider hygiene model alongside a dedicated hygiene assistant to increase access to care, improve efficiency, and elevate the patient experience.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver comprehensive periodontal care in accordance with all state dental board requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with a dedicated hygiene assistant to delegate non-clinical and preparatory tasks, maximizing chairside efficiency and patient access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain an efficient schedule that supports increased patient volume without compromising quality of care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate patients on periodontal health, disease prevention, and the connection between oral health and overall systemic health&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Dentist and care team on periodontal charting, treatment planning, and follow-up to support optimal patient outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dental hygiene licensure compliant with the State Dental Board with no adverse actions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a fast-paced or assisted/expanded hygiene model preferred, but not required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills with both patients and team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lead chairside care while working collaboratively with a hygiene assistant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient with Microsoft Office products and dental software; experience with Dentrix preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to delivering consistent, high-quality, patient-centered hygiene care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a valued team member, you’ll enjoy a rewarding career with growth opportunities and a comprehensive benefits package. Benefits for full-time Dental Hygienists include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical, Dental, and Vision Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Life Insurance, Short-Term and Long-Term Disability Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible Spending Accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellness Program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Time Off and Paid Holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quarterly Bonus Opportunities and incentives on hygiene products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Referral Program Bonuses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401k&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career Growth Opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
